## 7. GAP - Generic Access Profile {#gap}

### 7.1 What is a Profile {#gap-attribute}

The Generic Access Profile (GAP) handles how devices discover and connect to each other.

---

### 7.2 GAP Roles {#gap-roles}

Every BLE device plays one or more of these roles:

| Role | Definition | Example |
|------|-----------|---------|
| **Broadcaster** | Sends advertisements; doesn't accept connections | Beacon, temperature sensor |
| **Observer** | Listens for advertisements; doesn't initiate connections | Mobile app scanning for devices |
| **Peripheral** | Sends advertisements; accepts one connection | Heart rate monitor, headphones |
| **Central** | Listens for advertisements; initiates connections | Phone, laptop, smartwatch |

