## 15. Glossary {#glossary}

- **ATT:** Attribute Protocol - the wire format for GATT
- **BLE:** Bluetooth Low Energy
- **CCCD:** Client Characteristic Configuration Descriptor
- **CSRK:** Connection Signature Resolving Key
- **ECDH:** Elliptic Curve Diffie-Hellman key agreement
- **GAP:** Generic Access Profile (discovery & connection)
- **GATT:** Generic Attribute Profile (services & characteristics)
- **HCI:** Host Controller Interface (communication between host CPU and radio chip)
- **L2CAP:** Logical Link Control & Adaptation Protocol (channel routing)
- **LE:** Low Energy (another name for BLE)
- **LTK:** Long-Term Key (main encryption key)
- **MTU:** Maximum Transmission Unit (max data per transaction)
- **PHY:** Physical layer (the radio modes)
- **SMP:** Security Manager Protocol (pairing & encryption)
- **UUID:** Universally Unique Identifier (service/characteristic IDs)

---

**This is a comprehensive reference guide for understanding BLE from radio waves to application data. Each layer builds on the previous one, and together they enable efficient, secure wireless communication for IoT devices.**
